15class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE SyncStreamingDecoder : public StreamingDecoder {
16 public:
17 SyncStreamingDecoder(Isolate* isolate, WasmFeatures enabled,
18 CompileTimeImports compile_imports,
19 Handle<Context> context,
20 const char* api_method_name_for_errors,
21 std::shared_ptr<CompilationResultResolver> resolver)
22 : isolate_(isolate),
23 enabled_(enabled),
24 compile_imports_(compile_imports),
25 context_(context),
26 api_method_name_for_errors_(api_method_name_for_errors),
27 resolver_(resolver) {}
28
29 // The buffer passed into OnBytesReceived is owned by the caller.
30 void OnBytesReceived(base::Vector<const uint8_t> bytes) override {
31 buffer_.emplace_back(bytes.size());
32 CHECK_EQ(buffer_.back().size(), bytes.size());
33 std::memcpy(buffer_.back().data(), bytes.data(), bytes.size());
34 buffer_size_ += bytes.size();
35 }
36
37 void Finish(bool can_use_compiled_module) override {
38 // We copy all received chunks into one byte buffer.
39 auto bytes = std::make_unique<uint8_t[]>(buffer_size_);
40 uint8_t* destination = bytes.get();
41 for (auto& chunk : buffer_) {
42 std::memcpy(destination, chunk.data(), chunk.size());
43 destination += chunk.size();
44 }
45 CHECK_EQ(destination - bytes.get(), buffer_size_);
46
47 // Check if we can deserialize the module from cache.
48 if (can_use_compiled_module && deserializing()) {
49 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
50 SaveAndSwitchContext saved_context(isolate_, *context_);
51
52 MaybeHandle<WasmModuleObject> module_object = DeserializeNativeModule(
53 isolate_, compiled_module_bytes_,
54 base::Vector<const uint8_t>(bytes.get(), buffer_size_),
55 compile_imports_, base::VectorOf(url()));
56
57 if (!module_object.is_null()) {
58 Handle<WasmModuleObject> module = module_object.ToHandleChecked();
59 resolver_->OnCompilationSucceeded(module);
60 return;
61 }
62 }
63
64 // Compile the received bytes synchronously.
65 ModuleWireBytes wire_bytes(bytes.get(), bytes.get() + buffer_size_);
66 ErrorThrower thrower(isolate_, api_method_name_for_errors_);
67 MaybeHandle<WasmModuleObject> module_object = GetWasmEngine()->SyncCompile(
68 isolate_, enabled_, compile_imports_, &thrower, wire_bytes);
69 if (thrower.error()) {
70 resolver_->OnCompilationFailed(thrower.Reify());
71 return;
72 }
73 Handle<WasmModuleObject> module = module_object.ToHandleChecked();
74 resolver_->OnCompilationSucceeded(module);
75 }
76
77 void Abort() override {
78 // Abort is fully handled by the API, we only clear the buffer.
79 buffer_.clear();
80 }
81
82 void NotifyCompilationDiscarded() override { buffer_.clear(); }
83
84 void NotifyNativeModuleCreated(
85 const std::shared_ptr<NativeModule>&) override {
86 // This function is only called from the {AsyncCompileJob}.
87 UNREACHABLE();
88 }
89
90 private:
91 Isolate* isolate_;
92 const WasmFeatures enabled_;
93 const CompileTimeImports compile_imports_;
94 Handle<Context> context_;
95 const char* api_method_name_for_errors_;
96 std::shared_ptr<CompilationResultResolver> resolver_;
97
98 std::vector<std::vector<uint8_t>> buffer_;
99 size_t buffer_size_ = 0;
100};
101
102std::unique_ptr<StreamingDecoder> StreamingDecoder::CreateSyncStreamingDecoder(
103 Isolate* isolate, WasmFeatures enabled, CompileTimeImports compile_imports,
104 Handle<Context> context, const char* api_method_name_for_errors,
105 std::shared_ptr<CompilationResultResolver> resolver) {
106 return std::make_unique<SyncStreamingDecoder>(
107 isolate, enabled, compile_imports, context, api_method_name_for_errors,
108 std::move(resolver));
109}
